# Goose Hints - Project Conventions

## Language & Output
- Input documents (tenders/requirements) are in **Danish**.
- All analysis, summaries, and generated content must be in **English**.
- Always cite requirements by their **ID** (e.g., REQ-001, Krav 3.2) when referencing them.

## Output Formats
- Default output: **spreadsheet** (.xlsx) or **section files** in `docs/proposal/sections/`.
- Proposal section files go in `docs/proposal/sections/` (one file per section).
- Use spreadsheets for comparison matrices, scoring, compliance tracking, and requirement mappings.

## Decision Tracking
- The decision tracking spreadsheet is **not in this repo** — it is maintained externally.
- Do not create a `docs/decisions/` folder. Ask the user to provide the spreadsheet when needed.

## Model Performance
- If a response stalls or times out, break the task into smaller steps.
- Avoid generating very large single outputs — split into multiple files instead.
- Keep tool usage minimal per turn when working with cloud models.
- Recommended model for stability: `deepseek-v3.2:cloud` (faster time-to-first-token).
- Only 2 extensions should be enabled: `todo` and `developer`.

## WSL2 Environment
- This project may run in WSL2 using Windows Ollama via the API.
- Do NOT use the `ollama` CLI directly — use the Ollama HTTP API at `$OLLAMA_HOST` or `localhost:11434`.
- NTFS (`/mnt/c`) has limitations: `sed -i` fails, `git clone` needs `/tmp`, venvs need native Linux paths.
- When editing shell scripts, always use LF line endings (not CRLF).

## Project Structure
```
docs/
  proposal/
    sections/       # Individual proposal section files
  BEST-PRACTICES.md
  WEB-SEARCH-GUIDE.md
config/             # Goose config template, requirements
scripts/            # Setup and utility scripts
.agents/skills/     # Auto-discovered Goose skills
.goosehints         # This file — project conventions for Goose
```
